Owing to the multistep process a multilayered structure is expected. TEM cross section analysis shows a layered structure with higher density layers alternated to less dense ones (Fig. 1
                     ). The higher density layer consists of nanocrystals smaller than 5nm along the film thickness (darker regions in Fig. 1) embedded in an amorphous matrix, “confined” into each TiSiN single layer. The results are consistent with literature data of multilayer TiSiN films deposited by a CVD process similar to what used in this study [10]. The thickness of the layers is uniform, apart that of the first layer which has been grown on a different substrate (amorphous 


                              SiO


